  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IAstVisitor

    public final class StatementTypeChecker
extends ExpressionTypeChecker
    An instance of this class performs type usage checking on a statement.

        protected void infer(IExpression node,
         IExpressionType type)
        This method binds a type to an abstract-syntax-tree node.
        Parameters:

        type - is the type of the construct represented by the AST node.

      • condition

        protected void condition(IExpression expression)
        This method type-checks a condition expression.

        If the type-check fails, an error-report will be issued by the compiler.

        Parameters:
        expression - is the expression that is a condition.

      • assertType

        protected void assertType(IReturnType expected,
              IExpression expression)
        This method requires that the type of an expression is a subtype of a given type.

        If the type-check fails, an error-report will be issued by the compiler.

        Parameters:
        expected - is the expected type of the expression.
        expression - is the expression to type-check.

      • unaryOperation

        protected void unaryOperation(IUnaryOperation operation,
                  java.lang.String function,
                  IExpression operand)
        This method generalizes the resolution and type-checking of a unary operator.

        If the type-checking fails, an error-report will be issued by the compiler.

        Parameters:
        operation - is the unary operation itself.
        function - is the name of the static utility method that implements the operation.
        operand - is the only operand of the operation.

      • binaryOperation

        protected void binaryOperation(IBinaryOperation operation,
                   java.lang.String function,
                   IExpression left,
                   IExpression right)
        This method generalizes the resolution and type-checking of a binary operator.

        If the type-checking fails, an error-report will be issued by the compiler.

        Parameters:
        operation - is the binary operation itself.
        function - is the name of the static utility method that implements the operation.
        operand - is the only operand of the operation.

      • callStaticMethod

        protected void callStaticMethod(IExpression operation,
                    TypeSpecifier owner,
                    Name name,
                    java.lang.Iterable<IExpression> arguments)
        This method generalizes the resolution and type-checking of a static method invocation.
        Parameters:
        operation - is the invocation expression himself.
        owner - specifies the type that declares the invoked method.
        name - is the name of the invoked method.
        arguments - are the expressions that produce the invoked method's arguments.

      • findStaticField

        protected IField findStaticField(IExpression site,
                     TypeSpecifier type,
                     java.lang.String name)
        This method performs the resolution of a static-field.
        Parameters:
        site - is the site where the field is being used.
        type - is the type that contains the field.
        name - is the name of the field.
        Returns:
        the field that was found, or null, if no field was found.

      • findField

        protected IField findField(IExpression site,
               IExpression object,
               java.lang.String name)
        This method performs the resolution of an instance-field.
        Parameters:
        site - is the site where the field is being used.
        object - is the expression that produces the owner of the field.
        name - is the name of the field.
        Returns:
        the field that was found, or null, if no field was found.

      • declareVar

        protected void declareVar(Variable variable,
              IExpressionType type,
              boolean mutable)
        This method declares a local-variable and type-checks the declaration.
        Parameters:
        variable - is the variable to declare.
        type - is the type of the new variable.
        mutable - is false, iff the variable is readonly.
